[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Stretches the in-game day so you can fit more work into each sunrise. A full vanilla day lasts 7.5 minutes real-time — this mod lets you double or triple that without speeding anything else up.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Day-length multiplier[/b] — pick 1.5× (~11 minutes), 2× (15 minutes), 2.5× (~19 minutes) or 3× (22.5 minutes).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Affects the full day-night cycle[/b] — dawn, daytime, evening, and night all scale proportionally. NPC routines, plant growth, and work schedules tick against that same clock, so longer days let you get more production out of each in-game day before night forces you to sleep.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No unlock required[/b] — applies the moment the mod loads.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/73]Bring Out Yer Dead[/url] — schedule donkey deliveries at multiple times per day. Pairs brilliantly with a longer day.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — raises the "tired" threshold so you don't hit the sleep-debuff during an extended day.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/66]Regeneration Reloaded[/url] — passive energy regen. Keeps you going through longer productive days.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/41]Save Now[/url] — auto-save on new day so each stretched day ends with a fresh checkpoint.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

